page.title: 14Knotty Green - Beaconsfield
page.content: This area,just outside Beaconsfield, is a residential area,with large expensive houses.It is surrounded by picturesque scenery but does not have many public services such as telephone boxes and a local bus service.Most of the residents have two or more cars. There is extensive building work going on,mostly of houses.Despite it being a residntial area,there is not a lot for young people to do;there is one park,one{cricket ground and one {public house}.As well as these amenities there is a garage and a special school.The area is a commuter region with the businessmen driving to Beaconsfield to{travel}to London by train.Demand for houses is high so therefore houses are expensive.The main shopping centre is Beaconsfield with the new 'Waitrose' superstore.
